Debts for construction work
The programs of Habitat, Rescate de Espacios Públicos, and 3 x 1 provided social dwellings for migrants run the risk of because of lack of resources not to be completed or only with great delay, said Miguel Lopez Ángel Miranda.
The head of the Municipal Department of social development said that, although the works are already advanced, they now hover in danger, since the State Government not has paid her to resources, exceeding 11 million peso for the three programmes.
He said the total investment in these three programs is almost 50 million Peso which fell 25 per cent to the State. So far only the Federación and the community to the construction work would have funds contributed, why a delay of the completion is expected.
"12 Million must do it, and though the year to end, they gave us a penny, and that, although they have a us already in July would have to pay part", he said. "To be not too late, we have already begun with the construction of the work, and they are already well advanced, but we need the money."
He pointed out that under the rule of Jesus Aguilar Padilla Government not fulfilled his obligations is, which is why the community at the beginning of his reign had to borrow in the amount of 7 million. This would correspond to the amount that the Central Government would need to spend.
"That had gone to us already during the last parliamentary term, because the State did not have sufficient economic resources." "Continued the programs and this year we had to raise the funds us, that the State had not applied to take part in these programs," he carried out.
Even if the State authorities for the granting of those funds are obliged, he commented that in the Ministry of administration and finance, was requested to expedite the administrative work and to pay off the outstanding amount as soon as possible.
"Nearly 12 million must do it, and though the year to end, they gave us a penny."
